wiki.content: “Vultures” is the lead single of Kanye West and Ty Dolla $ign ’s joint album. This track was first heard when a sleep-disrupted fan posted a snippet to Snapchat, awoken by Kanye West listening to it in Al-Ula, Saudi Arabia on November 16, 2023. The following day, DJ Pharris played the track in its entirety on his Chicago radio station, Power 92. Shortly after the radio premiere, music blog owner Andrew Drive shared the uncensored version to X. Later that day, the song was uploaded to streaming services temporarily before being quickly removed. The cover art on the track was quickly retrieved. The song was officially released on streaming services on November 22, 2023, without Lil Durk’s verse, as well as Ye harmonising with Ty on the intro, amongst other minor changes. The Lil Durk version was officially released on streaming services on November 24, 2023 alongside the previous version. Read more on Last.fm.
